defaultClearly given the large number of primates in private ownership, professional facilities would be overwhelmed and unable to cope with an immediate ban. A more practical approach would be to have a ban with a grandfather clause which would allow current pri
defaultvate owners that are adhering to 
defaultthe 
defaultAnimal Welfare Act (2006) to keep their (non-breeding) primates. This app
defaultroach would stop the trade, phase out private keeping of primates as pets, and allow the worst cases, those that are not being kept according to t
